# Basic Linux Commands
cd --> Change Directory

pwd --> Prit Working Directory
ls --> List Contents of a Directory
cd .. --> Go back one directory
cd - --> Return to the previous directory
whoami --> Prints username
clear --> Clearing the screen
cp --> Copy
rm --> Remove
rmdir ==> "Remove directory" -- deleting an empty directory.
rm -rf ==> "Remove recursively force" -- deleting files and directories.
adduser --> Add user to the system
which --> shows the path of the file/used to determined the location of an executable file in the system.
apropos --> search the manual page descriptions for given a keyword.
sudo --> Super user
sudo chmod +rx <dir> --> Granting read and execute permissions for a directory.
sudo chown newowner:newowner <dir> ==> Changing ownership of a directory.
usermod ==> User modification
sudo usermod <username> --shell /bin/bash ==> Changing user's shell.
sudo useradd <username> -m ==> Creates a new user account and a corresponding home directory.
sudo ==> Super user do.
sudo su - <username> ==> Switching user.
sudo su - ==> Switching to a root user.
sudo visudo ==> Eding the sudoers file.
sudo userdel <username> ==> Deleting a user.
sudo groupadd <groupname> ==> Creating/Adding a group.
sudo usermod -aG <groupname> <username> ==> Adding a user to a group. (a --> append)
sudo gpasswd -d <username> <groupname> ==> Deleting a user from a group.
sudo userdel ==> Deleting a user.
sudo groupdel <groupname> ==> Deleting a group.
